reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: There have been times when I wish I had a paper towel or something other than a wet wipes when trying to clean up a mess. These dry wipes fit the bill completely.They’re soft but sturdy, and don’t tear easily. They can absorb quite a bit of liquid and that’s important with toddler spills.They also work great if you spill things as an adult!I do wish they were in a more travel friendly container.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Really nice quality wipes
reviews.reviewText: Make sure you realize that these are dry wipes but for me that's perfect as I don't usually like the solutions used in prepackaged wipes. These are really nice and easy to pull out of the package, and they hold up great without tearing apart. They're soft but still just abrasive enough to clean well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I used these to clean my dogs paws. She had dirt all over her paws so I used a wet wipe first and followed up with the dry wipe trying to knock off excess dirt and dry the off before turning her loose. They did a good job and didn't rip. I wouldn't describe these as soft, but they did a fine job cleaning my dog.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Serves a number of purposes
reviews.reviewText: I'm so glad that dry wipes are a thing. So many times I'd go to clean up a mess, wipe a nose, or clean up drool or something like that and be stuck doing the job with a wet wipe. I feel like these dry wipes offer a better approach when trying to clean up a baby or toddler. No worries of a cold wet wipe creating an uncomfortable moment. However, water can be added to create a wet wipe if desired. These dry wipes are certainly ideal in a variety of scenarios. I like that they're thick, eco-friendly, free from harsh chemicals, fragrances, and bleach. I have used them for a variety of things, including cleaning up a number of spills and messes. I'd like to stress the importance of not flushing these. They are not made to flush. The appropriate disposal is to throw them in the trash.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I can't even touch these without cringing. The feel of the wipes it's similar to those microfiber towels, and stick to my fingers. That said, others in my household have tried them, saying they are too thin and rough. I would not use these to wipe anything sensitive, such as a baby's bottom, or anyone's face.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I appreciate that these are biodegradable but these are so thin and feel cheaply made. I've used other dry baby wipes that are way softer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Quite expensive for the purpose.
reviews.reviewText: I use diaper wipes for a variety of things with personal care and with cleaning. Since these are not pre-moistened, these are more like single use towels that I use for drying my face after washing.Honestly, I find the pre-moistened wipes more beneficial. I prefer the wipes to already be wet enough to wipe up or clean something, otherwise I would use a paper towel.As far as using as intended, a diaper wipe, I find getting these wet before using an extra step I don’t usually make time for, so I would always use a traditional diaper wipe over these.You could moisten these yourselves, but the box these come in is paper, so you will need another container to store these in that case.Overall, quite expensive for the purpose…

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for various uses
reviews.reviewText: It basically feels like a dry disinfectant wipe. They're sorta soft and it actually works pretty good for things like cleaning or simple tissue usage. I can't attest to how good it works for a baby's buns tho
